name: Health Equity Alliance (HEAL)
directions: First floor, through front door on the left.
comment: Just tell the staff you needed to use the restroom, they’re all super friendly. They also offer free condoms, support groups, a food pantry, a needle exchange, harm reduction services, case management, and resources. Safe place for all LGBT+ people.

name: Health Equity Alliance (HEAL)
directions: Through front door, two gender-neutral single-stall, accessible bathrooms will be on your left-hand side
comment: Say you need to use a safe restroom! Staff are very understanding! They also offer condoms, dental dams, free HIV/Hep C tests, a food pantry, needle exchange and harm reduction, as well as case management services and are a great place for resources. Support groups for HIV/AIDS positive individuals and a LGBT youth (~12-21) support group, just ask staff for any assistance, all o them are super welcoming!
